CHETI PRAXIDES/ The body of a Lamu Polytechnic student who went missing at sea during a swimming expedition with friends three days ago has been recovered. Juma Mohamed, 23, went swimming in a group of about 30 of his classmates at Shella Beach in Lamu town. His body was recovered by diver Khalifa Abdulkadir at Shellaâ€™s Peponi Hotel shores at around 5.15am yesterday. The diver alerted his team who picked up the body and took it to the King Fahad Hospital morgue. He was buried shortly after.    